title: For Sale:  Rare 1984 Clayco Sports AK47
postcontent: Extremely rare 1984 Clayco Sports AK47. They are one of the earliest imports if not possibly even the first semi-auto AK47-type rifles to hit the US. This is a preban 100% Made in China by Norinco and imported before they started importing other Norincos and Polytechnology rifles. They were available with a standard fixed stock (black fiber-reinforced phenolic), or as an underfolder. The fixed stock guns were made at Ling Hua Arsenal and had polished bolts and bolt carriers. Included is the numbered matching detachable AKM style bayonet with scabbard, original cleaning kit, original mag and sling. I fired only two mags out of my AK47 many years ago and just cleaned the bore, bolt & carrier. The rest of the rifle still has the original cosmoline on some of the parts (see pics). 100% all original and numbers matching. Overall condition 98% +. The Clayco's are rumored to have been manufactured as close to Chinese military guns as possible.These Chicom rifles were featured in the September 1984 Edition of Soldier of Fortune Magazine. Included is an original 1984 Soldier of Fortune Magazine. Email me for many photos. I can also ship. No trades please.

title: For Sale:  60 rounds of WW2 Nazi marked /packaged collector ammo
postcontent:
This is collector ammo for the Austro-Hungarian Steyr military rifles that outfitted Austro-Hungarian Military forces at the time that these nations were incorporated into Germany at the outset of WW2.

These Steyr rifles were of a incompatible caliber with German Mauser rifles, so the Steyr guns were used largely as home guard weapons. Germany continued manufacturing ammunition for the Steyr rifles, in several runs during WW2, which is what is being offered in this lot of 6 complete original boxes of WW2 ammunition.

Each box contains two charging clips with 5 original rounds each of Nazi waffenampt marked Steyr ammo. There are a total of ten rounds and two proofed steel charging clips in each box. Most of the steel charging clips have a standard nazi waffenampt mark, however some of the clips were recycled by Nazi Germany and these bear austro-hungarian marks or austrian arsenal mark stamps.

You MUST have and present a valid Illinois FOID card at time of sale. No exceptions. 

I will sell two complete boxes of this ammo for $20 -
or all SIX complete boxes for $50.

please no trades, offers, shipping or negotiation. call 312 - nine two 7 - 67 four two

title: For Sale/Trade:  1906 M91 MOSIN NAGANT
postcontent:
This is one of the M91 rifles that were imported sometime in the 90's. They came from the balkans region, as the major manufacturer markings are scrubbed off, but from what I can tell it is still identifiable as a Tula, tang stamped 1906.

I've shot it on two different occasions, definitely not a tack driver, but the accuracy is decent for a gun that has been around the block for 100+ years. The flip up konovalov sight is measured in Arshin, and is much better than the notch and post on the regular 91/30.

This is not an M91/30, and this is not a $100 rifle. Handguards themselves can go for $50 (if you find someone willing to sell theirs).

Make me an offer, I will also take cash outright.

More images here: http://imgur.com/a/s7g5N

Originally used for training purposes and is distinguished by the straight-pull bolt action, the Schmidt-Rubin symbolizes what was once the heart of the Swedish army. title: For Sale:  NIB Kel-Tec KSG 12ga Shotgun - Black
postcontent:
Another unicorn at a great price!  Only *1* of these hard to come by shotguns available at this price right now.The KSG (Kel-Tec Shotgun) is Kel-Tec CNC’s first entry into the shotgun market. The size, shape, and design is similar to the currently available Kel-Tec RFB rifle, but the KSG ejects downward, instead of forward. The KSG weighs 6.9 lbs. and is as compact as legally possible with a 26.1” overall length and an 18.5” cylinder bore barrel. Even with this compact size, the internal dual tube magazines hold an impressive 12 rounds of 12 gauge 3” rounds in total (6 per tube). It can also reliably shoot shells as short as 1 3/4" up to the 3".
 
TECHNICAL SPECIFICATIONS

Caliber 12 gauge 3”
Barrel length 18.5"
Total capacity 6+6+1
Weight empty 6.9lbs
Weight loaded 8.5lbs
Finish Black
Length 26.1"
Height 7"

This simple and reliable pump action feeds from either the left or right tube. The feed side is manually selected by a lever located behind the trigger guard.
 
The pump includes an under picatinny rail for the mounting of a forward grip, a light, or a laser. The included top picatinny sight rail will accept many types of optics or iron sights. Forward and rear sling loops are built in, and a basic sling is included. The soft rubber butt pad helps to tame recoil.
 
The KSG receiver is made from hardened steel and includes the magazine tubes which have been welded in place. The grip and stock assembly is made of glass reinforced nylon (Zytel) and is easily disassembled by pushing out 2 pins, which store in 2 holes in the grip when removed. The barrel and pump assembly is removed by loosening the 2 front magazine tube nuts with a coin and sliding the assembly forward.
